data.description: Beautiful Downtown Franklin historic "Carpenter Build" home! From the charming porch, original wood work,wood floors, 9' ceilings to the original windows w/lead glass & storms, this home is a classic. Kitchen has some updates. Living & dining space is large & open and leads to glass french doors for the Parlor/Den. There is even a nice "Champion"sun-room on back side of main level. Upstairs has 3 bedrooms (all w/Walk-in closets) & an updated full bath. Outside back has big raised aggregate patio area, 20' retractable awning and then leads to a HUGE 3 car detached garage with heater, 220V RV plug & supported drive for RV. Home does have an older HVAC system and needs a little exterior work but all in all a very solid house and with the right buyers and a little updating, could become a very nice Franklin home!Roof 11 Yrs old with new gutters w/leaf guards.  HOME BEING SOLD AS-IS and priced accordingly but seller not aware of any defects
